As he grows older, he spirals into a life of painstruggling with depression, drug use, broken relationships, and self-destruction. Junji Ito uses disturbing and creepy artwork to show Yzs inner suffering, turning his mental illness into visual horror. The story includes very heavy topics like suicide, abuse, addiction, and trauma, so its not recommended for sensitive readers. Its based on a novel by Japanese author Osamu Dazai and shows how someone can feel completely lost and no longer human inside.
